President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Tracie Stevens as Chair of the National Indian Gaming Commission and Malcolm D. Jackson as Assistant Administrator for Environmental Information at the Environmental Protection Agency. Tracie Stevens has been serving as Senior Advisor to the Assistant Secretary for Indian Affairs at the Department of Interior since July 2009. She has experience in tribal issues such as gaming, law enforcement, energy, economic development, and natural resource rights. Stevens is a member of the Tulalip Tribes in Washington State and has been active in rebuilding the relationship between Tribes and the Department of Interior. Malcolm D. Jackson has recently served as the Senior IT Business Unit Director of CIGNA Insurance Disability Management Business. He has experience in IT strategy, enterprise resource planning, and business process re-engineering. Jackson is also involved in the Children's Literacy Initiative and the Jackson State University National Alumni Association. He holds a B.S. from Jackson State University and an M.B.A. from Northwestern University.